attributes.Long form description: The student disassembles the rolling cart. First, he flips the furniture and withdraws the four wheels. Then the student withdraws the trays beginning with the top one. Next, he unscrews the sidebars, removes them from the base frame, disassembles the base frame, and unscrews the sidebars.

attributes.Transcription: We will now disassemble the trolley from IKEA.
So please go ahead and disassemble it.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles all four wheels from the furniture.
The student disassembles the top basket.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student should not drop the nut.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the middle basket.
The student disassembles the bottom basket.
The student disassembles the two sidebars from the base frame.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student tries to disassemble the sidebar without unscrewing the hexagon cap nuts and bolts attached to it.
Student should not drop the screw.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles all legs of the sidebars and base frame.
